## Blue Nile Tennis Bracelet vs Tiffany

People compare these because Tiffany is the aspirational benchmark. Here's the honest picture:

| | Blue Nile | Tiffany |
|---|---|---|
| Classic 3ct tennis bracelet | $5,870 | ~$15,000–$22,000 |
| Lab-grown option | Yes — from $2,015 | No |
| Diamond quality disclosed | H-I/SI1-SI2 or F-G/VS2-SI1 | Not disclosed publicly |
| GIA certificate on bracelet | No (industry standard) | No |
| Safety clasp included | Standard box clasp | Lobster clasp, varies |
| Return policy | 30 days free | 30 days |
| Brand recognition as a gift | High | Iconic |

The price gap is real and structural. Tiffany charges for 125 years of brand equity, retail real estate, and the blue box. If the recipient specifically wants the Tiffany name, then only Tiffany delivers that. If you want the diamonds — Blue Nile is the rational choice.

